The paper proposes a deep generative model for joint distribution matching across multiple domains, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on scalability, which suggests that it may fall under the category of Large Scale Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of deep generative models and adversarial training suggests that it may also fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of mutual information, which is a common topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Statistical Learning (cs.SI).
